choices.text:
{
  "ingredients": ["fish fillets", "flour", "salt", "egg", "breadcrumbs", "oil"],
  "instructions": [
    "1. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).",
    "2. Rinse the fish fillets and pat dry with paper towels.",
    "3. In a shallow bowl, mix together the flour, salt, and pepper.",
    "4. In a separate shallow bowl, beat the egg.",
    "5. Place the breadcrumbs in a third shallow bowl.",
    "6. Dip the fish fillets in the flour mixture, then the egg, and finally the breadcrumbs.",
    "7. Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "8. Fry the fish fillets in the hot oil for 3 to 4 minutes on each side, or until golden brown and the fish flakes easily with a fork."
  ]
}
